					"_Name": "draw_rectangle",
					"_Deprecated": "false",
					"_ReturnType": "Undefined",
					"_Pure": "false"
				},
				{
					"Description": "With this function you can draw either an outline of a rectangle or a filled rectangle by defining an area where the (x1, y1) position is the top-left corner and the (x2, y2) position is the bottom-right corner. If it is filled you can define the individual colours for each corner point and if these colours are not the same, you will get a gradient effect from one to the other (the colour settings will override the base colour set with the function draw_set_colour()). Please note that the rectangle being drawn may need different values (+/-1 on the x, y, or width or height) to be drawn with the desired dimensions due to differences across the various supported platforms.",
					"Parameter": [
						{
							"_Name": "x1",
							"_Type": "Real",
							"_Optional": "false",
							"__text": "The x coordinate of the left of the rectangle."
						},
						{
							"_Name": "y1",
							"_Type": "Real",
							"_Optional": "false",
							"__text": "The y coordinate of the top of the rectangle."
						},
