				{
					"Description": "This function returns the x position of the touch on the device in relation to the GUI layer. If you are running this on a the HTML5 or PC and Mac modules then this value is updated constantly, as long as the device (usually a mouse) is plugged in, however for mobile devices, this will only be updated while the screen is being touched.\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\tNote that the maximum number of touches that can be detected will depend very much on the device being used and the OS it runs. Also note that on HTML5 only \"device 0\" will function correctly and other devices may give wrong values.",
