					"_Name": "arctan",
					"_Deprecated": "false",
					"_ReturnType": "Real",
					"_Pure": "true"
				},
				{
					"Description": "This function returns the inverse tangent (in radians) of a value given as a ratio y/x, where y = opposite side of triangle and x = adjacent side of triangle.\n\n\t\t\tUnlike arctan(), the function arctan2() is valid for all angles and so may be used to convert a vector to an angle without risking division by zero, and it also returns a result in the correct quadrant.",
