					"Description": "This function returns the inverse tangent (in degrees) of x.\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\tThis will accept any number as, unlike dtan(), darctan() asymptotes are on the y axis so it just means you'll never get returned a number greater than 90 or less than -90.",
